name: Alexander Rykunov
headline: Software Developer at BARS GROUP
creator: False
bio:
Passionate .NET Backend Software Developer With a Flair for Crafting Robust Solutions

I'm a dedicated .NET backend software developer driven by an insatiable curiosity and a love for crafting elegant, efficient solutions. With a keen eye for detail and a passion for clean, maintainable code, I thrive in the dynamic realm of software development.

Armed with a strong foundation in C#, .NET Core, and a host of backend technologies, I bring to the table a track record of architecting scalable, high-performance applications that stand the test of time. Whether it’s building RESTful APIs, optimizing database performance, or delving into the intricacies of asynchronous programming, I never shy away from a challenge!

My journey in software development has equipped me with a deep understanding of cloud technologies like Azure and AWS, allowing me to seamlessly integrate cloud services into my projects. Moreover, my familiarity with DevOps tools enables me to streamline the development pipeline, ensuring smooth, consistent delivery.

name: Aleksei Gerasev
headline: Solidity Developer
creator: False
bio:
My passion and dedication to the world of blockchain and smart contracts have become pivotal in my professional development. Currently, I am actively engaged in developing smart contracts using Solidity and diving deep into blockchain technologies. For me, this is not just a technology; it’s an opportunity to contribute to the future of digital innovations. I am also an active member of the Guide DAO community, which allows me to maintain close ties with professionals and stay updated on the latest trends in the blockchain space.

I have a strong interest in smart contract security, enabling me to create more reliable and secure solutions. Previously, I worked as a programming instructor, which allowed me to blend my extensive programming experience with the ability to effectively convey complex concepts. This experience not only aids my development work but also fosters my continuous learning and the ability to inspire others.

In my free time, I play the guitar and engage in sports, helping me maintain a healthy balance between work and personal life.

name: Suleiman karim eddin
location: Abu Dhabi Emirate, United Arab Emirates
headline: Fullstack | Nestjs  | React | Innopolis University
creator: True
bio:
As a dedicated software engineer at Innopolis University, I specialize in backend development with a strong focus on Golang and Docker. I also have substantial experience with React and Next.js. My journey in software engineering is marked by a commitment to continuous learning and improvement, with a proven work ethic recognized by peers and mentors.

I have accumulated practical experience through various projects and roles. From January to June 2023, I worked at whilelearn, applying my skills in ReactJS, Docker, and Golang to successfully develop and deploy a functional application, available at [whilelearn](https://www.whilelearn.com/). Additionally, my freelance career, spanning over three years, involved serving more than ten clients, delivering quality solutions using frameworks and languages such as NestJS, Laravel, and Spring Boot.

One notable project is my implementation of a microservices architecture using Golang, incorporating technologies like Fiber, SQLC, gRPC, PostgreSQL, and Docker Compose. This project is available for review at [Golang Microservices](https://github.com/SuleimanKarimEddin/go_microservices).

In addition to software development, I have contributed to research in quantum computing. I authored a seminal paper on "Quantum Microservices," published in "Advanced Information Networking and Applications" by SpringerLink, showcasing my expertise in integrating quantum computing with traditional software architectures. The paper can be accessed [here](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-031-57942-4_23).

My achievements include securing first place in the local World Robotics Olympiad (WRO) events in 2014 and 2017, representing my country internationally in Russia and Costa Rica. Additionally, I achieved second place in the GoOpenSource hackathon, marking my early contributions to the open-source community.

Fluent in Arabic and English, I am equipped to collaborate in diverse environments. I am eager to bring my skills, enthusiasm, and dedication to dynamic software development projects. You can reach me via email at sulimankareem90@gmail.com or connect with me on LinkedIn [here](https://www.linkedin.com/in/suleiman-karim-eddin-432024215/). My work and projects are also showcased on my [GitHub profile](https://github.com/SuleimanKarimEddin/).

name: Ivan Obraztsov
headline: Senior Frontend Developer | Web Developer | Computer Science Graduate
creator: False
bio:
Hey! I'm Ivan Obraztsov, a seasoned Frontend Developer.

Why I Love What I Do:

I thrive on turning ideas into interactive web experiences. The ever-evolving nature of web development keeps me hooked, and I absolutely love the challenge.

Key Values and Principles:

Innovation Matters: I love projects that push boundaries and demand creative solutions.
Collaboration is King: Cross-functional teamwork is my secret sauce to delivering cohesive solutions.
Communication is Key: Whether it's code or concepts, I make sure everyone's on the same page.
Personality Traits and Work Outcomes:

I'm the go-to guy for injecting positivity into the team. My knack for clear communication ensures that even complex technical concepts are digestible for everyone. Flexibility is my forte; I thrive in dynamic environments and see challenges as opportunities.

Growth and Development:

Constantly evolving is my mantra. From Tinkoff Fintech courses to summer internships at Outofstock and Innopolis University, I'm always chasing that next level of expertise. Volunteering at Innopolis University keeps me grounded, reminding me of the importance of giving back.

Professional Skills:

JavaScript (TypeScript) and React are my playmates.
Redux is my trusted ally for state management.
HTML, CSS (SCSS), and Webpack are part of my daily toolkit.
Project management with Trello keeps me on track.
Fluent in both Russian (native) and English (proficiency).
Domain Knowledge:

Spearheaded the development of an Asset Management System for fleet management.
Enhanced fleet management efficiency by over 2 times with the RadarIT AMS system.
Architected and developed applications from scratch, leaving a trail of success.
Feel free to reach out if you're interested in a collaboration or just want to geek out about frontend development. Thanks for stopping by! 🚀

Contact me:

name: Yaroslav Avdiev
headline: Strategy director | Non-Executive Director | Chief Digital Transformation Officer
creator: False
past_company_2: YourLift LLC / Intellectual Solutions for Engineering Systems
bio:
Over 10 years of experience in business management. Created and implemented development and digitalisation strategies in the following industries: manufacturing, housing and utilities, engineering, tourism, and HR-tech.

STRATEGY
Designing digital systems; building functional, object and logical data models; structuring and optimising business processes, with the use of digital systems. 
Experience in designing, piloting and implementing digital and management solutions for business growth.
Future state vision development and presentation, and subsequent distribution into business lines. 
Visionary strategy development at the level of the future economic paradigm.

BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT MANAGEMENT
Risk assessment, creation and implementation of strategic development plans, adaptation of business strategy to current changes and levels of risk (adaptation to external environment).
Experience in launching new digital products, developing and implementing industry digitalisation programmes.
Effective interaction with a wide range of stakeholders.
Experience of building and managing project teams, including IT teams, creating and implementing corporate KPIs and reward systems for staff of varied seniority.
Building highly effective teams with up to 30 direct reports.
Experience in delivering presentations and public speaking in Russian, English and German.

FINANCE AND INVESTMENT
Track record of developing and implementing a range of measures aimed at increasing companies’ market capitalisation.
Experience in attracting private and corporate investors (domestic and foreign), and in obtaining state subsidies and grants. 
Systematic liaising with government agencies, including executive authorities of various constituencies of the Russian Federation, at the level of federal ministries, including the Ministry of Construction and the Ministry of Industry and Trade of the Russian Federation.
Experience in structuring complex investment deals, including projects with an annual financing volume exceeding 1 billion rubles, and an economic potential of up to 25 billion rubles per year.
The average deal cycle of 0.5 - 1.5 years, with companies’ turnover growth from 0 to over 100 million rubles per year.
Considerable expertise in budgeting and pricing at Director level.
Experience in corporate reporting and auditing. 

PERSONAL QUALITIES AND SKILLS
Highly productive in multi-tasking and in periods of strategic uncertainty. 
Entrepreneurial mindset and the ability to see the business structure "from above", a helicopter view.

name: Kristina Posashkova
headline: Frontend Developer
creator: False
bio:
Frontend-developer

JavaScript, TypeScript, HTML5, SCSS, Figma, Adobe Photoshop, React, Redux Toolkit, Git, GitHub, GitLab, Responsive Layout, Semantic Markup, BEM, REST API, React Router, Webpack, Gulp, API, Vite, Directus, GraphQL, VueJS, Nuxt, Astro, HTMX, Express.js, Node.js, Lottie Animation, Chart.js.

-------------------------------------------------------
Верстка (адаптивная, семантическая)
-Создание удобных и адаптивных веб-страниц с использованием HTML, CSS, SCSS.
-Обеспечение кросс-браузерной совместимости и оптимизация верстки.
JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Vue, Nuxt

Разработка интерактивных интерфейсов с использованием React и Vue.
-Опыт работы с серверным рендерингом (SSR) на базе Nuxt.js и Express.js.
-Оптимизация кода для повышения производительности, включая lazy loading.

Работа с формами и API
-Интеграция и обработка данных с использованием REST API и GraphQL.
-Работа с формами, валидация и взаимодействие с конечными точками API.
HTMX, Astro

Применение HTMX для динамического обновления контента без перезагрузки страниц.
-Разработка статичных и динамических сайтов с использованием Astro.

Управление состоянием (Redux)
-Эффективное управление состоянием приложений с помощью Redux.

Работа с админкой через GraphQL (Directus)
-Настройка взаимодействия с административной панелью через GraphQL.

name: Hadi Salloum
headline: Researcher @ Innopolis University | Q Deep Founder | Quantum Computing | Astrophysics
creator: False
bio:
With a strong academic background, my journey commenced with notable achievements in international Physics Olympiads, securing an honorable mention at the esteemed International Physics Olympiad (IPhO) Lithuania 2021. As a Senior Coach, I led 50 students and organized impactful Physics Olympiad training sessions, showcasing adaptability and a dedicated commitment to education.

My research pursuits converge on two key fronts. Firstly, I am deeply involved in enhancing computer software applications through the potential of quantum computing. Additionally, I actively explore the intriguing intersection between physics and computer science, particularly within the domains of astrophysics and artificial intelligence. This two-pronged approach aims to advance quantum computing applications while uncovering fresh insights at the confluence of physics and computer science, driving progress in both fields.

In the realm of research projects in Russia, I focused on refining deep learning models for language models and advancing data-driven solutions for brain tumor segmentation. Concurrently, mentoring Bachelor students in quantum computing applications, aligning their research with lab objectives, and contributing to presentations has been a fulfilling aspect of my journey.

Beyond academia and research, my passion for politics thrives. Exploring the dynamics of political systems and their societal impacts fascinates me, offering a holistic perspective that complements my scientific endeavors.

In essence, my diverse experiences showcase an unwavering commitment to academic excellence, innovation, and a multifaceted interest in physics, computer science, and the intricate dynamics of politics. These experiences serve as a springboard for further contributions toward advancing knowledge and technology within these interlinked spheres.

name: Rustam Sadykov
headline: Java Developer – Innopolis University
creator: False
bio:
После получения высшео образования в 2009 году, устроился в дочернюю компанию ПАО "Газпром": ООО "Газпром трансгаз Казань".
Первые 3 года занимался обслуживанием и ремонтом линейной части магистральных газопроводов в качестве трубопроводчика линейного и, затем, мастера.
С 2012 года перешел в Инженерно-технический центр ООО "Газпром трансгаз Казань", где занимался анализом технического состояния магистральных газопроводов. Начинал инженером 2 категории и спустя 3 года стал заместителем начальника отдела анализа технического состояния линейной части магистральных газопроводов и газораспределительных станций.
Основной процесс: анализ и мониторинг технического состояния магистральных газопроводов. Цель: в условиях дефицита рабочей силы, материальных ресурсов и времени сформировать перечень мероприятий обеспечивающий заданный уровень технического состояния магистральных газопроводов.

Достижения: абсолютно все математические алгоритмы ПАО "Газпром" в области анализа технического состояния, выбора ремонтых технологий и оценки ресурса, реализованы мною в програмном коде (Visual Basic for Application), что обеспечило быстрое и объективное принятие решения о необходимых мероприятиях для обеспечения безаварийной эксплуатации магистральных газопроводов.



С 2020 года основным местом работы стал Центр нефтегазовых технологий АНО ВО "Университет Иннополис", где принято участие в коммерческом проекте в качестве эксперта технического диагностирования магистральных газопроводов. Кроме этого, получен опыт ведения backlog в качестве бизнес и системного аналитика, devops-инженера.

В период 2022.01 по 2023.05 - вел небольшой коммерческий проект, в котором был на нескольких ролях в качестве руководителя проектов, инженера, технического писателя, тестировщика, бизнес-аналитика, системного аналитика, backend-разработчика, devops-инженера. По итогу получен бесценный опыт на всех позициях типового состава проектной группы, кроме frontend-разработчика.

С 2023.05 работаю и непрерывно совершенствуюсь в качестве разработчика ПО. На текущий момент реализовал несколько сервисов для компании ПАО "Татнефть":
1. Оценка обводненности скважин;
2. Отбраковка результатов гидродинамических исследований;
3. Сервис хранения данных полученных с приборов;
4. Сервис валидации данных полученных с приборов
и прочие.
Текущий стек: Java 8-22, Hibernate, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, Docker, k8s, Maven, Gradle, Asure DevOps (TFS), Git, Kafka, RabbitMQ, REST API
